Version 1.02 introduced a test suite to test the major subsystems of
extproc_perl outside of production.  For this to work at all, the ExtProc
module was linked statically (no .so file) with the extproc_perl.so shared
object.  However, the presence of a previous installation of the ExtProc
module (a shared version) will cause the tests to fail miserably.  To fix this,
remove the old version of the ExtProc module as follows:

0) Check to make sure nothing is using extproc_perl before proceeding!!!

1) Find the top-level ExtProc directories in your Perl installation and remove
   them:

   $ find `perl -MConfig -e 'print $Config{sitelib}'` -type d -name ExtProc
   /usr/local/perl/5.8.0-shared/lib/site_perl/5.8.0/i686-linux/auto/ExtProc

2) Find ExtProc.pm and remove it:

   $ find `perl -MConfig -e 'print $Config{sitelib}'` -name ExtProc.pm
   /usr/local/perl/5.8.0-shared/lib/site_perl/5.8.0/i686-linux/ExtProc.pm

COMMENT: You can remove these files from within the find command itself, but I
typically don't like to tempt fate with my primary perl installation!  ;-)
